{"questionId":"9376","questionHtml":"<p>Find <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sigma \">\n  <mi>σ</mi>\n</math></span>, the standard deviation of <em>X</em>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>use of inverse normal to find z score&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>z</em>&nbsp;= −1.0598</p>\n<p>correct substitution&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{24.15 - 25}}{\\sigma } =&nbsp; - 1.0598\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>24.15</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>25</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>σ</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1.0598</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sigma \">\n  <mi>σ</mi>\n</math></span> = 0.802&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1 &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9376","referenceCode":"SPM.2.SL.TZ0.8b.i","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find σ , the standard deviation of X.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.8—Binomial distribution","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.9—Normal distribution and calculations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}